A tragic shooting incident at an Omaha mall left eight dead, including employees and shoppers.
The shooter, Robert A. Hawkins, had a troubled past with a history of criminal offenses.
He entered the mall with an assault rifle, targeting victims at random.
Hawkins left a note expressing remorse before taking his own life.
The community is in shock, with President offering condolences and support.
The incident adds to a series of school shootings in the country, highlighting the ongoing issue of gun violence.
Grief counseling is being offered to those affected by this senseless tragedy.
